2026-05-27 11:08:06,597 [openai._base_client] DEBUG: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'headers': {'X-Stainless-Helper-Method': 'chat.completions.parse'}, 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-ceb41cea-ae3e-46b5-936a-ca89687e19b5', 'post_parser': <function Completions.parse.<locals>.parser at 0x1280e1ee0>, 'security': {'bearer_auth': True}, 'content': None, 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'You are an accounts receivable specialist drafting a collections email on behalf of LedgerShield Inc.\n\nCLIENT DETAILS:\n  Client Name   : Orion Dynamics\n  Amount Due    : $4,200.00 USD\n  Days Overdue  : 18 days\n  Contact Email : finance@oriondynamics.com\n\nESCALATION TIER: FIRM_REMINDER\nTONE INSTRUCTIONS: Use a professional and direct tone. Reference the client\'s payment terms explicitly. Assume good faith — treat the overdue balance as an oversight — but be clear and unambiguous about the urgency and expectation for immediate payment.\n\nPRIOR EMAIL HISTORY (oldest first):\n  Date: 2026-04-09\n  From: ar@ledgershield.com\n  To: finance@oriondynamics.com\n  Subject: Invoice AR-1041 – $4,200.00 Due May 9, 2026 – LedgerShield Inc.\n  Body:\nHi Marcus,\n\nPlease find attached Invoice AR-1041 for services rendered in March 2026. A summary is below for your reference:\n\n  Invoice Number : AR-1041\n  Invoice Date   : April 9, 2026\n  Amount Due     : $4,200.00\n  Payment Due    : May 9, 2026\n  Payment Terms  : Net-30\n\nThis invoice covers the LedgerShield platform subscription and onboarding support for Q1 2026 as outlined in your service agreement.\n\nPayment can be made via ACH (preferred), wire transfer, or check. Our remittance details are included on the attached invoice. Please reference AR-1041 on your payment.\n\nDon\'t hesitate to reach out if you have any questions or if your team needs a revised remittance format.\n\nBest regards,\nSophia Reeves\nAccounts Receivable | LedgerShield Inc.\nar@ledgershield.com | +1 (415) 882-3300\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\nDraft a collections email appropriate for the escalation tier. The email must:\n1. Open with a clear, direct reference to the outstanding invoice and amount.\n2. Reference prior communications where relevant.\n3. State a specific payment deadline (within 7 days).\n4. Apply the tone described above without deviation.\n5. Include a professional sign-off from the LedgerShield AR team.\n\nFill all fields of the CollectionsEmail model:\n  - recipient: the client\'s billing contact email (finance@oriondynamics.com)\n  - client_name: exactly "Orion Dynamics"\n  - subject: a concise subject line referencing the overdue balance\n  - body: the complete email body text\n  - escalation_tier: exactly "firm_reminder"\n'}], 'model': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'response_format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'json_schema': {'schema': {'properties': {'recipient': {'title': 'Recipient', 'type': 'string'}, 'client_name': {'title': 'Client Name', 'type': 'string'}, 'subject': {'title': 'Subject', 'type': 'string'}, 'body': {'title': 'Body', 'type': 'string'}, 'escalation_tier': {'enum': ['firm_reminder', 'legal_notice', 'final_demand'], 'title': 'Escalation Tier', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['recipient', 'client_name', 'subject', 'body', 'escalation_tier'], 'title': 'CollectionsEmail', 'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False}, 'name': 'CollectionsEmail', 'strict': True}}, 'stream': False}}
